Introduction 	  Measuring is an important science skill. Other skills needed to do science include keeping records, doing calculations, organizing data, and making models. Knowing how to stay safe while doing scientific investigations may be the most important skill of all. You will read about all these science skills in this lesson. 
Measuring 	  One of the most important aspects of measuring is the system of units used for measurement. Remember the Mars Climate Orbiter that opened this chapter? It shows clearly why a single system of measurement units is needed in science. 
