Introduction 	  Most of the chemical reactions you have seen so far in this chapter are synthesis reactions. In this type of reaction, two or more reactants combine to synthesize a product. There are several other types of chemical reactions, including decomposition, replacement, and combustion reactions. You will read about all four types of reactions in this lesson. Table 8.1 summarizes the four types of chemical reactions you will read about in the rest of the lesson. You can see demonstrations of each type at this URL: URL . 
