Speed = 3 m1 wave/s = 3 m/s 	  You Try It! Problem: Jera made a wave in a spring by pushing and pulling on one end. The wavelength is 0.1 m, and the wave frequency is 0.2 m/s. What is the speed of the wave? If you want more practice calculating wave speed from wavelength and frequency, try the problems at this URL: http ://URL . The equation for wave speed (above) can be rewritten as: 
